        "name": "A full-body undead shipwright pirate character, large and burly, standing front-facing with a powerful heavy build. He looks like a cursed sailor who repairs ships, with pale gray-blue undead skin, glowing teal-blue eyes, a grim weathered face, and a long rough gray beard. He wears a dark red pirate bandana, messy hair, and a torn navy-blue pirate coat over dirty off-white work clothes. His clothing is rugged, layered, and practical: leather belts, buckles, straps, tool pouches, rope wraps, metal hooks, small repair tools, and torn brown trousers.\n\nHe has a right peg leg, made from dark wood with metal bands and rope bindings. His other leg wears a heavy worn leather boot. One hand holds a large blocky carpenter\u2019s hammer with a rectangular wooden head, metal reinforcements, and a sturdy handle. The other hand carries a wooden crate/toolbox full of ship supplies, including rope, wood pieces, repair tools, and metal parts. The crate has iron bands and a faded anchor symbol.\n\nHis arms should look strong and undead, with cracked glowing teal veins or ghostly markings. Add a faint sea-ghost aura around him, like blue-green mist rising from his shoulders and arms. The character should feel like a haunted repair specialist, not a captain: more worker, builder, and ship mechanic than fancy noble pirate.\n\nStyle: dark gothic pirate fantasy, gritty nautical concept art, weathered sea-worn textures, muted colors, deep navy, brown leather, dirty cream cloth, rusted metal, ghostly teal highlights. Clear full-body character design, centered, no background clutter. Keep the silhouette readable: big coat, hammer on one side, supply crate on the other, right peg leg visible. (copy 2)",
